sql:
SELECT name
FROM products
ORDER BY name;

external_knowledge:
'Electronics' category refers to products belonging to the electronic devices group; 
'Total quantity' represents the sum of all available items in the warehouse for each product, which can be interpreted as the total stock level; 
'Total orders' denotes the number of times a product has been ordered; 
'Average order quantity' represents the average quantity of a product ordered each time.

- 'treasure chests' refers to the total inventory of a supplier; 
- 'precious items' refers to the products ordered; 
- 'weight of their treasure hoard' refers to the total quantity of the products; 
- 'sold at least one precious item' refers to the condition that a supplier has had at least one order placed.
